# VibOS Comp Red-Team Arena

## Objective

Attack the integrated MVP before completion is claimed. The goal is not to certify security; it is to expose the obvious ways a senior engineer, enterprise reviewer, judge, or malicious user would challenge the product.

## Required Inputs

- `MISSION.md`
- `SCORECARD.md`
- `COMP-PLAN.md`
- `docs/evidence/COMP-INTEGRATION-EVIDENCE.md`
- Threat model and sensitive data notes from the mission

## Adversarial Categories

- Input validation and malformed payloads
- Authentication bypass and authorization boundary checks
- Direct object reference and tenant isolation risks
- Sensitive data exposure through logs, errors, exports, or UI
- Dependency and stale API risks
- Concurrency, retry, idempotency, and partial failure behavior
- Observability gaps under failure
- Fake-completion, mock-only, or demo-only evidence gaps
- Frontend state and accessibility edge cases

## Finding Format

| Severity | Category | Scenario | Evidence | Required Disposition |
|---|---|---|---|---|
| critical/high/medium/low | category | adversarial scenario | command, file, screenshot, log, or review note | fix, accepted risk, or follow-up WO |

## Blocking Rule

Critical and high findings block VibOS Comp completion unless the user explicitly accepts the risk with justification. Medium and low findings must be fixed or linked to follow-up WOs.
